# Voice-to-Sculpture Studio — Technical Specification v2.0
**Date:** November 20, 2025  
**Version:** 2.0 (Optimized for High-Performance Web)  
**Target Stack:** Svelte 5 (Runes), Threlte (WebGPU), Web Audio (Worklets), Hybrid AI (WebLLM/Cloud).

## 0. Core Vision & Architecture
A browser-based creative instrument that transforms vocal audio into 3D ceramic forms. It prioritizes "game feel" (real-time responsiveness), physical metaphors (pressure/tension over raw data), and privacy-first architecture.

### 0.1 System Boundary
The application runs entirely in the browser (Client-side).
- **Render Loop:** Decoupled from Main Thread via Threlte/Three.js.
- **Audio Processing:** Runs in `AudioWorklet` (Real-time) and Web Worker (Analysis) to prevent UI jank.
- **Storage:** Uses **OPFS (Origin Private File System)** for high-performance local saving.
- **AI:** Hybrid strategy allowing **Local** (In-browser WebLLM) or **Cloud** (OpenAI-compatible REST) generation.

---

## 1. Technology Stack (Strict)

- **Framework:** SvelteKit (Static Adapter).
- **State Management:** Svelte 5 Runes (`$state`, `$derived`, `$effect`).
- **3D Engine:**
  - **Three.js** (r170+).
  - **Renderer:** `WebGPURenderer` (primary), falling back to WebGL2 if unsupported.
  - **Wrapper:** **Threlte v9+** (Svelte 5 native).
  - **Shading:** TSL (Three.js Shading Language) for materials.
- **Audio Pipeline:**
  - **API:** Web Audio API.
  - **Pattern:** `AudioWorkletProcessor` for capture.
  - **Transport:** `SharedArrayBuffer` with `RingBuffer` pattern for zero-copy data transfer.
  - **Analysis Library:** `Essentia.js` (Wasm) or `Meyda` running inside a Web Worker.
- **Storage:** Native **OPFS** API (accessed via `opfs-tools` wrapper for simpler DX).
- **AI Inference:**
  - Local: `@mlc-ai/web-llm` (WebGPU acceleration).
  - Cloud: Standard `fetch` to OpenAI-compatible endpoints.
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4.

